<title>PORTUGAL: Portuguese bond report.</title>
<headline>Portuguese bond report.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1996-10-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bonds closed with strong gains, resisting some late profit-taking in Spain, and the Spanish market will continue to set the pace on Thursday, traders said.</p>
<p>Non-resident interest along the yield curve helped to correct some imbalances with cash spreads narrowing with Spain.</p>
<p>The Portuguese short end is trading at a premium to Spain while the longer end is at a discount.  </p>
<p>Surging hopes that Spain will qualify for Economic and Monetary Union (EMU) -- and Portugal is objectively already better placed -- lay beyind the sharp price rises.</p>
<p>The Bank of Portugal is also seen as cutting its repo rate again soon.</p>
<p>--Sergio Goncalves, Lisbon bureau 3511-3150035</p>
